						               													<description>This is a game for ages 14 and up. The box contains a board, 8 pawns, cards and an hour-glass.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The cards contain numbers (1 to 6) and words.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;On your turn you have to call a number, take a card from the stack and read the word next to the number you have called. You write down the first word that comes into your mind. The other players have now to guess one by one what word you have written down.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;If someone guesses the right word you can both move your pawn 2 fields on the board. If no one was able to guess the right word, everybody can guess as long as the hour-glass keeps running (45 sec). If someone is able to guess the right word now, you can both move your pawn one field on the board.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The first player to reach the destination field on the board is the winner of the game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
